<blockquote>
  <h3 id="ä¾‹å­">ä¾‹å­</h3>
  <p>G and K are negotiating a friendly acquisition of K by G. The management teams at both companies have agreed upon a transaction value of about $27 per share for Kâ€™s stock, but are presently negotiating alternative methods of payment. Nagy, CFA, works for the investment banking firm representing G.</p>
</blockquote>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>ä¼°å€¼æ¯”ç‡</th>
      <th>G</th>
      <th>K</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>åˆå¹¶å‰è‚¡ä»·</td>
      <td>$36</td>
      <td>$24</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>æµé€šè‚¡ä»½æ•°</td>
      <td>50M</td>
      <td>24M</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>åˆå¹¶å‰å¸‚å€¼</td>
      <td>$1,800M</td>
      <td>$576M</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>ååŒä½œç”¨çš„NPV</td>
      <td>$120M</td>
      <td>-</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<blockquote>
  <p>Calculate the post-merger value of the combined firm, gains accrued to the target, and gains accrued to the acquirer under the following scenarios:</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <ul>
    <li>Case 1: Cash offer of $27 per share for Kâ€™s stock</li>
    <li>Case 2: Stock offer of 0.75 shares of Gâ€™s stock per share of Kâ€™s</li>
  </ul>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <h3 id="answer">Answer</h3>
  <p>å› ä¸º$36 Ã— 0.75 = 27ï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥ä¸¤ç§æ”¶è´­æ–¹å¼çš„æ”¶è´­ä»·æ˜¯ä¸€æ ·çš„</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <h4 id="case-1">Case 1:</h4>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <ul>
    <li>Cash price = $27 Ã— 24M = $648M</li>
    <li>V<sub>AT</sub> = $1,800M + $576M + $120M - $648M = $1,848M</li>
    <li>Gain<sub>T</sub> = $648M - $576M = $72M</li>
    <li>Gain<sub>A</sub> = $120M - $72M = $48</li>
  </ul>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <h4 id="case-2">Case 2:</h4>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <ul>
    <li>V<sub>AT</sub> = $1,800M + $576M + $120M - $0 = $2,496M
      <ul>
        <li># shares target received = 24M Ã— 0.75 = 18M</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>P<sub>AT</sub> = $2,496M / (50M + 18M) â‰ˆ $36.7</li>
    <li>P<sub>T</sub> = 18M Ã— $36.7 = $660.60M</li>
    <li>Gain<sub>T</sub> = $660.60M - $576M = $84.6M</li>
    <li>Gain<sub>A</sub> = $120M - $84.6M = $35.4M</li>
  </ul>
</blockquote>

